%I A396625 #29 Jul 12 2026 23:47:07
%S A396625 1,1,3,17,351,107857
%N A396625 Number of antichains of nonempty integer compositions that contain at least one composition of n and no compositions greater than n.
%C A396625 Here a composition A = (a_1,a_2,...a_m) covers B = (b_1,b_2,...b_m) iff a_i >= b_{i+k} for all b_i in B and some k >= 0.
%H A396625 John Tyler Rascoe, <a href="/A396625/a396625.py.txt">Python code</a>.
%e A396625 The antichain {(1,1,1,1), (2,1,1), (1,2), (3)} contains a composition of 4 and no other elements are compositions of weight greater than 4, so this is counted under a(4) = 351.
%e A396625 a(0) = 1: {}.
%e A396625 a(1) = 1: {(1)}.
%e A396625 a(2) = 3: {(1,1)}, {(1,1), (2)}, {(2)}.
%e A396625 a(3) = 17: {(1,1,1), (2)}, {(3), (1,1)} and the 15 antichains containing only compositions of 3.
